6
Strategic Sourcing & Category Management 
Define and execute procurement strategies for packaging, raw materials, warehouse supplies, and ancillary products.
Segment procurement into categories (corrugated boxes, films, tapes, sustainable packaging, machinery, etc.) and build category road-maps.
Lead supplier segmentation, rationalization, and consolidation plans to optimize cost, quality, and risk.
Collaborate with R&D / design teams to evaluate new materials or sustainable alternatives (e.g. compostable films, biodegradable polymers) in line with DCGPac’s EcoPac / RePac initiatives.


Supplier Identification, Onboarding & Development 
Source and evaluate domestic and global suppliers (local manufacturers, overseas vendors) for quality, cost, delivery reliability, and compliance.
Perform supplier audits, due diligence, capability assessments, and capacity checks.
Lead supplier onboarding, contract negotiation, and integration.
Drive supplier development & continuous improvement programs (quality, lead times, process upgrades, ESG practices).


Negotiation & Contract Management 
Lead negotiation of prices, terms & conditions, payment terms, delivery SLAs, penalty clauses, exclusivity, warranties, etc.
Draft and manage supplier agreements, NDAs, master procurement contracts, legal & compliance review.
Establish and enforce performance structures: KPIs, SLAs, scorecards, escalation mechanisms.


Procurement Operations & Execution 
Issue RFx (RFQ, RFP, RFI), evaluate responses, perform bid comparison and select optimal vendors.
Raise and manage purchase orders, monitor order fulfillment, delivery schedules, logistics coordination.
Track lead times, manage buffer stock, safety stock, reorder points.
Monitor and resolve procurement exceptions — delays, short shipments, quality rejections, mismatches.


Quality & Compliance Assurance 
Work closely with QC / quality control labs to ensure material compliance, testing, certifications, and standards.
Ensure supplier compliance with applicable statutory, environmental, and safety requirements.
Incorporate compliance and ESG / sustainability clauses into contracts.


Cost Management, Analytics & Reporting 
Develop and track procurement KPIs: cost savings, spend under management, supplier on-time delivery, quality rejects, procurement cycle time, etc.
Use data analytics and spend analysis to find opportunities for savings, vendor consolidation, demand aggregation.
Prepare procurement budget, forecasts, and monitor actuals vs plans.
Conduct regular reviews with stakeholders to assess procurement performance.


Risk Management & Sustainability 
Identify supply chain risks (supplier insolvency, raw material volatility, geopolitical, regulatory) and devise mitigation strategies (dual sourcing, buffer stocks).
Lead initiatives to adopt sustainable packaging options, circular supply (RePac), reduce waste and support ESG goals.
Monitor industry trends, raw material price fluctuations, regulatory changes, and feed into procurement strategy.


Cross-Functional Collaboration & Stakeholder Management 
Interface with design, operations, logistics, sales, and R&D teams to align procurement with business needs, BOM changes, demand forecasts, etc.
Serve as procurement subject matter expert in new product development, cost-down programs, packaging innovation projects.
Collaborate with finance for payment terms, vendor risk analysis, working capital management.


Team Leadership & Process Optimization 
Manage and mentor a team of procurement buyers/analysts.
Define roles, objectives, metrics, training and development.
Establish standardized procurement processes, tools, workflows, and best practices.
Drive automation, digital procurement tools (e-procurement, supplier portals, analytics dashboards).
